WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:08.138
<i>- Previously
on "Resident Alien"...</i>

00:08.182 --> 00:09.705
<i>- Oh!
- Aah!</i>

00:09.748 --> 00:11.141
<i>- So what happened to the real
Harry Vanderspeigle?</i>

00:11.185 --> 00:12.838
- I don't know.

00:12.882 --> 00:14.579
- Dr. Vanderspeigle,
a new doctor has arrived.

00:14.623 --> 00:17.321
- Please call me Dr. Ethan.
- I'm glad you know about me.

00:17.365 --> 00:19.410
- Nobody wants to hide
who they really are.

00:19.454 --> 00:22.152
- You should stop feeling
guilty about giving away Jay.

00:22.196 --> 00:25.286
She is a survivor.

00:25.329 --> 00:27.331
[gasping] <i>
- He will die.</i>

00:27.375 --> 00:29.681
- My leg--
chop it off.

00:29.725 --> 00:30.900
- Aah!

00:30.943 --> 00:32.728
<i>- If Asta wasn't there,
I would be dead.</i>

00:32.771 --> 00:35.209
- They took your spaceship,
didn't they?

00:35.252 --> 00:36.601
That means they're after you.

00:36.645 --> 00:40.257
It's probably M.I.B.--
men in black.

00:40.301 --> 00:41.693
<i>- I invited a friend over
with her husband.</i>

00:41.737 --> 00:43.652
This is Sarah
and Richard Houston.

00:43.695 --> 00:45.175
<i>You can babysit Max
whenever you want.</i>

00:45.219 --> 00:47.003
<i>- Oh, I would love that.</i>

00:47.047 --> 00:48.048
<i>- You shouldn't
have taken that.</i>

00:48.091 --> 00:49.440
[beeps]

00:49.484 --> 00:50.963
<i>Now the kid's gonna know
we were in his room.</i>

00:51.007 --> 00:52.530
- Good.

00:52.574 --> 00:54.228
Then when he goes to warn it,
we'll be right on its tail.

00:54.271 --> 00:56.621
- Asta!
Are you in there?

00:56.665 --> 00:58.841
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:58.884 --> 01:00.712
[screams]

01:00.756 --> 01:02.801
<i>- ♪ If you kiss her,
you'll know it ♪</i>

01:02.845 --> 01:04.586
<i>♪ You'll never forget</i>

01:04.629 --> 01:07.850
<i>♪ She's a little
French sweetheart... ♪</i>

01:07.893 --> 01:10.157
<i>- Everyone has to die.</i>

01:10.200 --> 01:11.854
<i>It is the normal
cycle of life</i>

01:11.897 --> 01:14.857
<i>for beings across
the entire universe.</i>

01:14.900 --> 01:16.554
<i>Some may live longer
than others,</i>

01:16.598 --> 01:18.861
<i>but every organism
comes into being</i>

01:18.904 --> 01:21.168
<i>and then ceases being.</i>

01:21.211 --> 01:23.387
<i>♪</i>

01:23.431 --> 01:27.348
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

01:27.391 --> 01:29.437
<i>The animals know this.</i>

01:29.480 --> 01:31.221
<i>They live in harmony
with the Earth,</i>

01:31.265 --> 01:33.571
<i>as it was meant to be.</i>

01:33.615 --> 01:37.662
<i>Everyone I kill with my device
is going to die anyway.</i>

01:37.706 --> 01:40.926
<i>At least I'm killing them
for a good reason.</i>

01:40.970 --> 01:42.537
<i>♪</i>

01:42.580 --> 01:44.626
<i>It's different for humans.</i>

01:44.669 --> 01:47.194
<i>Humans kill because they know
they're small,</i>

01:47.237 --> 01:49.500
<i>insignificant, weak.</i>

01:49.544 --> 01:52.764
<i>And killing makes them
feel strong...</i>

01:52.808 --> 01:55.158
<i>even if it's just
for a moment.</i>

01:55.202 --> 02:02.339
<i>♪</i>

02:19.617 --> 02:22.185
[sighs]

02:22.229 --> 02:24.840
[glass clinking]

02:24.883 --> 02:31.847
<i>♪</i>

02:41.552 --> 02:44.425
<i>And when humans are smart,</i>

02:44.468 --> 02:47.776
<i>they may even get away
with murder.</i>

02:47.819 --> 02:50.170
<i>♪</i>

02:50.213 --> 02:53.173
[glass clinking]

02:53.216 --> 02:56.001
<i>♪</i>

02:56.045 --> 02:59.179
[wind howling]

03:02.791 --> 03:07.317
<i>Of course, no being really
gets away with anything.</i>

03:07.361 --> 03:09.014
[radio glitches on and off]

03:09.058 --> 03:12.017
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

03:12.061 --> 03:14.106
<i>♪</i>

03:14.150 --> 03:16.935
<i>The universe knows
what you have done,</i>

03:16.979 --> 03:19.938
<i>even if nobody else does.</i>

03:19.982 --> 03:21.940
[wind howling]

03:21.984 --> 03:26.031
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

03:26.075 --> 03:29.034
[wind howling]

03:29.078 --> 03:33.822
<i>♪</i>

03:33.865 --> 03:36.041
<i>And the universe
will restore balance</i>

03:36.085 --> 03:37.826
<i>one way or another.</i>

03:37.869 --> 03:41.003
<i>♪</i>

03:41.046 --> 03:43.048
<i>Humans have a word for this.</i>

03:43.092 --> 03:44.485
<i>♪</i>

03:44.528 --> 03:46.356
<i>They call it "karma."</i>

03:46.400 --> 03:49.229
<i>♪</i>

03:50.142 --> 03:53.233
<i>[mid-tempo guitar music]</i>

03:53.276 --> 04:00.240
<i>♪</i>

04:01.110 --> 04:02.894
[car doors close]

04:02.938 --> 04:05.027
- I thought you said
Asta's car was here.

04:05.070 --> 04:06.507
- Oh.
Calling me a liar?

04:06.550 --> 04:08.204
- Well, if the shoe fits,
D'arce.

04:08.248 --> 04:09.684
- Please don't fight.

04:09.727 --> 04:11.294
Look, D'arce, we're all just
freaking out a little bit.

04:11.338 --> 04:12.556
Like, this is bad.

04:12.600 --> 04:13.992
- You damn near
gave me a heart attack

04:14.036 --> 04:15.559
banging on my door like that
at the crack of dawn.

04:15.603 --> 04:17.909
- Oh, I'm so sorry
that finding the dead body

04:17.953 --> 04:19.694
of the man I love
locked in a freezer

04:19.737 --> 04:21.739
is so inconvenient for you!

04:21.783 --> 04:24.481
All right?
It's a human life, asshole.

04:24.525 --> 04:26.178
Okay?
Harry is dead.

04:26.222 --> 04:29.312
[door opens]

04:29.356 --> 04:31.532
- What is going on out here?
- [chuckles]

04:31.575 --> 04:33.577
I'm standing here wondering
why I ain't home in bed.

04:33.621 --> 04:35.100
- Thank God you're alive.

04:35.144 --> 04:37.320
- This is--no, it's impossible.

04:37.364 --> 04:40.236
- She is worse than your dog.

04:40.280 --> 04:43.283
- Yeah, well, I didn't have
the heart to wake Cletus up.

04:43.326 --> 04:45.285
He was in REM sleep
chasing goats.

04:45.328 --> 04:47.069
- I'll get her.

04:47.112 --> 04:48.462
- Sorry about this, Dr. V,

04:48.505 --> 04:50.942
but, uh, D'arcy broke
into your cellar last night

04:50.986 --> 04:52.988
and she thinks she saw
a dead you in the freezer.

04:53.031 --> 04:54.468
- Mm.
- I told her it was probably

04:54.511 --> 04:55.773
just some meat in there
that looked like you,

04:55.817 --> 04:56.948
like a frozen pig or something.

04:56.992 --> 04:58.776
- I am more handsome
than a pig.

04:58.820 --> 05:00.474
- Oh, me too.
Yeah, man, I'm probably

05:00.517 --> 05:02.127
somewhere between a pig
and a dolphin.

05:02.171 --> 05:04.347
You know, that dolphin,
that's a fine-ass animal.

05:04.391 --> 05:06.044
[chuckles]

05:06.088 --> 05:09.309
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

05:09.352 --> 05:10.788
- It's nothing but meat.

05:10.832 --> 05:13.878
- You moved the body.
- Sure enough.

05:13.922 --> 05:15.010
And here it is.

05:15.053 --> 05:16.403
- No, I meant
the dead guy, dipshit.

05:16.446 --> 05:17.708
Obviously it's not him,

05:17.752 --> 05:19.188
but I saw
a dead body down there.

05:19.231 --> 05:20.537
<i>♪</i>

05:20.581 --> 05:22.409
Why was Asta's car outside?

05:22.452 --> 05:24.411
- We went to a medical
conference together.

05:24.454 --> 05:26.021
You smell like alcohol.

05:26.064 --> 05:27.805
- Okay, come on, D'arce.
You have to go now.

05:27.849 --> 05:29.981
I'll buy you breakfast.
- No.

05:30.025 --> 05:31.809
No!
[scoffs]

05:31.853 --> 05:34.290
I know what I saw.
Stop trying to gaslight me.

05:34.334 --> 05:35.509
I know I'm not crazy.

05:35.552 --> 05:38.163
- The deputy said...

05:38.207 --> 05:39.164
it's time to go.

05:39.208 --> 05:40.209
- What? No.

05:40.252 --> 05:41.515
No!
- Let's--

05:41.558 --> 05:43.473
- Get your ------- hands
off me!

05:43.517 --> 05:44.605
- Oh, dear.

05:44.648 --> 05:46.041
- Ah!
Help me, Deputy!

05:46.084 --> 05:49.044
She on me like a spider!
- Dish it out--

05:49.087 --> 05:52.613
<i>- It's unfortunate I have to
kill everyone and leave here.</i>

05:52.656 --> 05:55.311
<i>The warmth of spring
is just arriving.</i>

05:55.355 --> 05:58.706
[indistinct shouting]

05:58.749 --> 06:00.360
- Ow!

06:00.403 --> 06:02.144
- Let go of my damn hair!
Ah!

06:02.187 --> 06:04.407
- Let go of his hair.
- Ah, get your damn--

06:04.451 --> 06:06.670
- D'arcy, let go of the chair.
- [D'arcy spits]

06:06.714 --> 06:07.845
- Yes.
- Take that!

06:07.889 --> 06:10.370
- You spit--
- It is quite nice here.

06:10.413 --> 06:11.501
- Handcuffs,
that's what they're for.

06:11.545 --> 06:12.894
They're for cuffing hands!

06:12.937 --> 06:15.200
Come on.
Come on.

06:15.244 --> 06:16.419
I give you credit.
- Okay.

06:16.463 --> 06:17.594
- You fight like a pack
of pit bulls.

06:17.638 --> 06:18.900
- Ugh, come on, hit me!

06:18.943 --> 06:21.424
You know you want to
hit me, Sheriff.

06:21.468 --> 06:23.165
Do it!
- Please stop struggling!

06:23.208 --> 06:25.210
It's gonna be okay,
I'll drive your car back.

06:25.254 --> 06:26.429
- Ow!
- Get in the car!

06:26.473 --> 06:28.126
- I'm sorry about this, Doctor.

06:28.170 --> 06:31.869
- Yes, I'm very upset
at this intrusion.

06:31.913 --> 06:33.044
[car horn honks]

06:33.088 --> 06:34.350
- "I'm gonna read you
your rights."

06:34.394 --> 06:35.699
What do I say?

06:35.743 --> 06:37.527
Tell me what I say!

06:37.571 --> 06:38.702
- That's the problem.
[D'arcy grunts]

06:38.746 --> 06:41.226
- Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

06:41.270 --> 06:43.751
Okay, all right, all right,
all right, all right.

06:43.794 --> 06:46.928
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

06:46.971 --> 06:53.935
<i>♪</i>

06:57.460 --> 07:00.550
[knife thudding]

07:03.814 --> 07:05.816
- [whispering] Pull it up.
I have to see this.

07:05.860 --> 07:07.209
- Aye.

07:08.602 --> 07:11.561
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

07:11.605 --> 07:17.437
<i>♪</i>

07:17.480 --> 07:19.569
[whispering]
There, she's stealing it.

07:19.613 --> 07:20.918
- I knew it.

07:20.962 --> 07:25.140
She's a woman in a purple
skirt, man in black.

07:25.183 --> 07:27.185
- We have to warn Harry.

07:27.229 --> 07:30.362
<i>♪</i>

07:30.406 --> 07:33.278
<i>[mid-tempo dramatic music]</i>

07:33.322 --> 07:40.242
<i>♪</i>

07:46.204 --> 07:48.642
- Told you he'd lead us
to the alien.

07:48.685 --> 07:52.210
[engine turning over]

07:52.254 --> 07:55.170
[steering wheel squeaking]

07:59.435 --> 08:01.045
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:01.089 --> 08:02.394
- You want to tell me
what happened?

08:02.438 --> 08:04.658
I'm worried about you.
- You're overreacting.

08:04.701 --> 08:06.660
It's not like you've never
bailed me out of jail before.

08:06.703 --> 08:08.531
- "Overreacting"?
Cool.

08:08.575 --> 08:10.228
I woke up this morning
to a hundred texts

08:10.272 --> 08:11.969
and a voicemail
from you screaming,

08:12.013 --> 08:13.275
"He's dead!
He's dead!"

08:13.318 --> 08:15.364
- All right, look,
I know what happened.

08:15.407 --> 08:18.106
All right?
You and Harry murdered a guy.

08:18.149 --> 08:19.411
It happens,
but I'm here for you.

08:19.455 --> 08:20.804
We're gonna take my car
to Canada.

08:20.848 --> 08:22.458
From there, I've got an old
ski buddy in Juneau.

08:22.502 --> 08:25.287
There's a safe deposit box,
1,000 bucks to keep us going.

08:25.330 --> 08:28.420
Three passports.
So...

08:28.464 --> 08:30.901
- That's... a lot to process.

08:30.945 --> 08:33.730
Uh, but, no,
I did not kill anyone.

08:33.774 --> 08:35.210
- Are you sure?

08:35.253 --> 08:38.213
- [scoffs]
I'd remember.

08:38.256 --> 08:40.868
- Right.
Right.

08:40.911 --> 08:43.131
Cool, so the Sheriff was right.
I'm seeing things.

08:43.174 --> 08:46.264
New low.
- D'arcy, what did you do?

08:46.308 --> 08:48.615
- I sort of broke
into Harry's house last night,

08:48.658 --> 08:51.095
and I saw a freezer
full of meat,

08:51.139 --> 08:53.576
and I thought
it was a dead body.

08:53.620 --> 08:55.926
- [sighs] D'arce,
how much did you have to drink?

08:55.970 --> 08:57.537
- Barely anything to drink.

08:57.580 --> 09:01.584
I had a couple edibles
and a pill I found in my couch.

09:01.628 --> 09:03.586
- Come on!
- Look...

09:03.630 --> 09:06.807
you're obviously keeping
some big secret from me.

09:06.850 --> 09:08.025
- You're my best friend!

09:08.069 --> 09:11.115
I would not keep secrets
from you.

09:11.159 --> 09:12.943
- You're lying.
- No, I'm not.

09:12.987 --> 09:14.728
- Yes, you are.
- No.

09:14.771 --> 09:16.207
- You have a tell, remember?

09:16.251 --> 09:17.992
When you're lying,
you get overly huggy

09:18.035 --> 09:19.820
and touchy.

09:19.863 --> 09:21.517
- That's not true.

09:22.953 --> 09:24.476
D'arce, come on.

09:24.520 --> 09:26.000
- Thanks for bailing me out.
I got to go.

09:26.043 --> 09:27.958
- D'arcy.

09:28.002 --> 09:31.788
<i>[mid-tempo guitar music]</i>

09:31.832 --> 09:34.269
God.

09:34.312 --> 09:39.622
<i>- ♪ Runaway, I'm just
a runaway, yeah, yeah ♪</i>

09:39.666 --> 09:41.972
<i>♪ Runaway, I want to...</i>

09:42.016 --> 09:44.279
- Slow down.
You're too close.

09:44.322 --> 09:46.324
- Jesus Christ, it's like
driving with my grandmother.

09:46.368 --> 09:47.978
"Why don't you go
out back, Memaw,

09:48.022 --> 09:49.980
and knit me a sweater?"

09:50.024 --> 09:51.678
[metal crunching,
brakes squeal]

09:51.721 --> 09:53.680
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

09:53.723 --> 09:55.159
[sighs]

09:55.203 --> 09:57.988
<i>♪</i>

09:58.032 --> 10:00.512
Great, you distracted me, now
we're losing the little shit.

10:00.556 --> 10:03.994
- Oh, my God.
Are--are you all right?

10:04.038 --> 10:06.997
- Watch your language, please.

10:07.041 --> 10:10.044
And you owe me $100
for the bike.

10:10.087 --> 10:11.872
- Um...

10:11.915 --> 10:13.134
looks fine to me.

10:13.177 --> 10:15.702
- I'd be happy
to wait for the police.

10:15.745 --> 10:16.920
- Pay the girl.

10:16.964 --> 10:18.966
You're the one who made me
run her over.

10:19.009 --> 10:20.358
Let's go.

10:20.402 --> 10:21.838
Now we've lost him.

10:21.882 --> 10:23.927
<i>♪</i>

10:23.971 --> 10:26.451
- Pleasure.
[RV door closes]

10:26.495 --> 10:29.672
- Taking so long.
- It's $100.

10:29.716 --> 10:32.632
<i>[flute music playing
over radio]</i>

10:32.675 --> 10:35.025
<i>- My device is at full power.</i>

10:35.069 --> 10:37.724
<i>With one press of the button,
the timer will begin,</i>

10:37.767 --> 10:40.074
<i>and roughly
90 Earth minutes later,</i>

10:40.117 --> 10:43.251
<i>8 billion humans
will cease to exist.</i>

10:43.294 --> 10:45.035
<i>This is the moment
I fulfill the mission</i>

10:45.079 --> 10:47.821
<i>that will change the course
of the universe forever.</i>

10:47.864 --> 10:49.997
<i>- [over radio]
Are you dreaming of pizza?</i>

10:50.040 --> 10:51.520
<i>Mama Sap's Pizza is now open</i>

10:51.563 --> 10:54.001
<i>in the heart
of downtown Patience!</i>

10:54.044 --> 10:55.742
- [groans]

10:55.785 --> 10:58.701
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

10:58.745 --> 11:00.660
<i>♪</i>

11:00.703 --> 11:04.054
<i>I can't kill everyone on Earth
with an empty stomach.</i>

11:04.098 --> 11:06.535
<i>[Iris DeMent's "Our Town"]</i>

11:06.578 --> 11:09.930
<i>- ♪ And you know
the sun's setting fast ♪</i>

11:09.973 --> 11:14.674
<i>♪ And just like they say,
nothing good ever lasts ♪</i>

11:14.717 --> 11:17.589
<i>♪ Well, go on, now,
and kiss it goodbye ♪</i>

11:17.633 --> 11:19.722
<i>♪ But hold on to your lover</i>

11:19.766 --> 11:22.986
<i>♪ 'Cause your heart's
bound to die ♪</i>

11:23.030 --> 11:28.078
<i>♪ Go on, now,
and say goodbye to our town ♪</i>

11:28.122 --> 11:31.038
<i>♪ To our town</i>

11:31.081 --> 11:35.346
<i>♪ Can't you see the sun
setting down on our town? ♪</i>

11:35.390 --> 11:37.218
- Is Jay working here?

11:37.261 --> 11:39.742
- I gave her a part-time job.

11:39.786 --> 11:42.440
- Dad, I don't think
that's a good idea.

11:42.484 --> 11:45.879
- You're friends with an alien,
and Jay's a bad idea?

11:47.271 --> 11:49.665
- Oh, she's coming over.
Get out of here!

11:49.709 --> 11:52.755
<i>♪</i>

11:52.799 --> 11:54.452
- Hey.

11:54.496 --> 11:55.845
- Hey.
[chuckles]

11:55.889 --> 11:58.282
Um, I see you have a new job.

11:58.326 --> 11:59.806
- Yeah.
First day.

11:59.849 --> 12:01.808
- Cool.

12:01.851 --> 12:04.811
- Look, D'arcy told me
what happened on the mountain.

12:04.854 --> 12:06.856
Just wanted to make sure
you didn't lose

12:06.900 --> 12:09.163
any fingers or toes
or anything.

12:09.206 --> 12:11.121
- Uh, no.
Um...

12:11.165 --> 12:13.863
[chuckles nervously]
Got 'em!

12:13.907 --> 12:15.560
Look, I was gonna tell you

12:15.604 --> 12:18.128
that if you ever want to talk
about...

12:18.172 --> 12:21.653
everything, anything, I'm here.

12:21.697 --> 12:24.787
- You want me to talk to you
about you?

12:24.831 --> 12:27.224
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:27.268 --> 12:28.704
- Well...

12:28.748 --> 12:30.271
I was thinking we could--
- No.

12:30.314 --> 12:31.620
- Sure.
Yeah.

12:31.663 --> 12:33.230
- You know, I should
get back to work.

12:33.274 --> 12:36.103
- Of course.
It was nice to see you.

12:36.146 --> 12:39.323
<i>♪</i>

12:39.367 --> 12:40.890
Hello.
- Hello.

12:40.934 --> 12:43.240
- Hello, Miss Twelvetrees.

12:43.284 --> 12:45.286
<i>♪</i>

12:45.329 --> 12:47.331
- Help yourself.

12:47.375 --> 12:49.594
- I know that you know.

12:51.379 --> 12:53.468
- [scoffs]

12:53.511 --> 12:56.123
I know that you know.

12:56.166 --> 12:58.342
Does she know?

12:58.386 --> 13:00.257
- "She" has a name.

13:00.301 --> 13:01.824
And she knows.

13:01.868 --> 13:04.871
She knows a lot.

13:04.914 --> 13:07.308
<i>♪</i>

13:07.351 --> 13:09.266
We have a situation.

13:09.310 --> 13:11.181
- The government is after him.

13:11.225 --> 13:13.227
They know that I know
who he is.

13:13.270 --> 13:15.185
- What?
How?

13:15.229 --> 13:16.839
- Because they're
the government.

13:16.883 --> 13:18.928
Don't be so naive.

13:18.972 --> 13:20.190
- Excuse me?

13:20.234 --> 13:21.713
- I'm sorry.

13:21.757 --> 13:23.672
Sometimes I speak to adults
like they're my peers

13:23.715 --> 13:26.066
because I'm mature for my age.

13:26.109 --> 13:27.894
I'm working on it.

13:27.937 --> 13:29.373
- I hid a camera in my room,

13:29.417 --> 13:31.288
and I saw them search my house.
- What?

13:31.332 --> 13:32.724
- And they went back
to their base,

13:32.768 --> 13:34.726
and now they're driving around
searching for him.

13:34.770 --> 13:37.991
- How do you know
where their base is?

13:38.034 --> 13:40.341
- We have our ways.

13:40.384 --> 13:43.300
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:43.344 --> 13:47.304
<i>♪</i>

13:47.348 --> 13:50.307
- [sighs]
Where is my phone?

13:50.351 --> 13:55.312
<i>♪</i>

13:58.968 --> 14:01.101
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:01.144 --> 14:02.493
<i>- I learned from the squirrels</i>

14:02.537 --> 14:04.147
<i>that when you've filled
your stomach,</i>

14:04.191 --> 14:07.368
<i>you should take as much food
as you can to eat later.</i>

14:07.411 --> 14:09.892
<i>With this pizza stack,
I can kill everyone</i>

14:09.936 --> 14:12.895
<i>and still have pizza
to eat for days.</i>

14:12.939 --> 14:14.679
<i>And now, with a belly
that's bursting</i>

14:14.723 --> 14:16.856
<i>like a stuffed garbage bag,</i>

14:16.899 --> 14:20.555
<i>there's nothing stopping me
from completing my mission.</i>

14:20.598 --> 14:26.430
<i>♪</i>

14:26.474 --> 14:28.389
I should test it first.

14:28.432 --> 14:31.218
<i>♪</i>

14:31.261 --> 14:32.784
- Okay, you two.

14:32.828 --> 14:35.657
I'll be upstairs on the
treadmill if you need anything.

14:35.700 --> 14:37.746
Sahar, thank you again for
helping Max with his homework.

14:37.789 --> 14:39.095
- I don't mind.

14:39.139 --> 14:41.576
I want to be a teacher
when I'm old, like you.

14:41.619 --> 14:43.186
- Wow.

14:43.230 --> 14:45.667
I'm not old.
I'm young, okay?

14:45.710 --> 14:47.974
My life is not passing me by.

14:48.017 --> 14:51.542
I'm just--just living it.
But that's--that's wonderful.

14:51.586 --> 14:54.458
It's just wonderful.

14:54.502 --> 14:59.333
<i>♪</i>

14:59.376 --> 15:01.726
[electronic beeping]

15:01.770 --> 15:03.119
<i>♪</i>

15:03.163 --> 15:05.861
- This... makes no sense.

15:05.905 --> 15:08.037
It says the phone is here.

15:08.081 --> 15:09.604
- You're tracking
the wrong phone.

15:09.647 --> 15:11.519
Put it on your mom's.

15:11.562 --> 15:13.651
- It is on my mom's.

15:13.695 --> 15:15.175
- It can't be.

15:15.218 --> 15:18.613
I put your mom's phone
right under the RV.

15:18.656 --> 15:25.533
<i>♪</i>

15:29.493 --> 15:31.321
- Lock the front door.
I'll get the back.

15:31.365 --> 15:38.198
<i>♪</i>

15:38.241 --> 15:40.461
- [whispering]
Don't be afraid.

15:40.504 --> 15:42.463
We just need your help.

15:42.506 --> 15:44.944
- I'm not giving
your 100 bucks back.

15:48.512 --> 15:55.476
<i>♪</i>

16:01.221 --> 16:03.136
<i>- My device uses
the Earth's own energy</i>

16:03.179 --> 16:05.312
<i>to send a pulse
throughout the world</i>

16:05.355 --> 16:07.444
<i>that will kill every human.</i>

16:07.488 --> 16:10.143
<i>I can also direct it
to a singular point</i>

16:10.186 --> 16:13.015
<i>and get rid of this body.</i>

16:13.059 --> 16:17.367
<i>♪</i>

16:17.411 --> 16:20.327
- Will it hurt?

16:20.370 --> 16:21.850
[bones cracking]

16:21.893 --> 16:24.505
- You again?

16:24.548 --> 16:27.377
- You know
you're just stalling.

16:27.421 --> 16:29.510
You're afraid to kill everyone.

16:29.553 --> 16:31.860
- No, I'm not.

16:31.903 --> 16:34.167
My people do not feel fear.

16:34.210 --> 16:37.083
- Yes, but you're not
your people anymore, are you?

16:37.126 --> 16:40.738
You've been infected
with humanity.

16:40.782 --> 16:43.480
- I don't need to listen
to this!

16:43.524 --> 16:47.354
- I was supposed to die
of old age with Isabelle.

16:47.397 --> 16:49.965
I even bought a plot
in Upstate New York

16:50.009 --> 16:53.403
under the most beautiful
maple tree.

16:53.447 --> 16:56.058
We were supposed to be
next to each other forever.

16:56.102 --> 16:58.452
<i>♪</i>

16:58.495 --> 17:00.062
- Do you miss her?

17:00.106 --> 17:03.718
- I miss a lot of things...

17:03.761 --> 17:07.243
the five senses...

17:07.287 --> 17:10.812
driving around
with nowhere to go...

17:10.855 --> 17:13.684
tacos.

17:13.728 --> 17:16.383
But I loved Isabelle.
- How do you know?

17:16.426 --> 17:19.168
- How do I know
I loved my wife?

17:19.212 --> 17:21.649
- What did it feel like?

17:21.692 --> 17:23.433
<i>♪</i>

17:23.477 --> 17:26.001
- It feels like...

17:26.045 --> 17:28.873
life.

17:28.917 --> 17:31.050
Like everything
you've ever felt.

17:31.093 --> 17:35.054
The joy and the fury
held in your heart

17:35.097 --> 17:38.274
and wrapped in...

17:38.318 --> 17:40.407
hope...

17:40.450 --> 17:44.280
hope that everything
will be okay.

17:44.324 --> 17:47.327
Love makes you feel
connected to everything.

17:47.370 --> 17:49.807
Make you feel light-headed,
you feel like you're floating.

17:49.851 --> 17:51.679
- I love Isabelle, too.

17:51.722 --> 17:54.595
- You're an asshole.
You don't even know her!

17:54.638 --> 17:57.032
- I do.

17:57.076 --> 18:00.035
When she left...

18:00.079 --> 18:01.950
my heart felt
like it was falling.

18:01.993 --> 18:03.430
- That's rejection.

18:03.473 --> 18:04.909
That's not love.

18:04.953 --> 18:08.391
- Then why do I feel
the other things?

18:08.435 --> 18:11.046
I feel hope.

18:11.090 --> 18:13.614
I feel connected to everyone...

18:13.657 --> 18:15.094
to everything.

18:15.137 --> 18:18.271
- I used to feel those things.

18:18.314 --> 18:20.099
You took it all from me.

18:20.142 --> 18:23.841
<i>♪</i>

18:23.885 --> 18:25.582
- I'm sorry.

18:25.626 --> 18:28.194
- You didn't just take Isabelle
away from me.

18:28.237 --> 18:31.501
When you killed me,
you took me away from Isabelle.

18:31.545 --> 18:33.938
She needs me.

18:33.982 --> 18:35.026
- Stop.

18:35.070 --> 18:37.464
Stop doing that with your eyes.

18:37.507 --> 18:41.207
- When you killed me,
you killed her.

18:41.250 --> 18:42.817
- No.
- Yes!

18:42.860 --> 18:44.253
She cries every day.

18:44.297 --> 18:46.168
- No.
No, she doesn't.

18:46.212 --> 18:47.474
- You broke her heart!

18:47.517 --> 18:48.518
- Stop!

18:50.564 --> 18:53.523
[phone buzzing]

18:53.567 --> 18:55.743
<i>♪</i>

18:55.786 --> 18:58.180
[phone chimes]

18:58.224 --> 19:00.661
- Harry, uh,
where are you?

19:00.704 --> 19:02.141
Please call me
when you get this.

19:02.184 --> 19:03.316
I need to talk to you.

19:03.359 --> 19:04.839
- Hey, Asta.
How you doing?

19:04.882 --> 19:06.536
- Oh, hey.
Um...

19:06.580 --> 19:09.409
I need to leave early.
Is that okay?

19:09.452 --> 19:11.193
- That's fine.
It's slow.

19:11.237 --> 19:12.934
I'll hold down the fort.

19:12.977 --> 19:15.719
- Okay.
Thank you.

19:18.505 --> 19:20.985
- Hey, Asta,
can you help me out?

19:21.029 --> 19:22.944
I need that dead foot.

19:22.987 --> 19:24.337
- Really?
- Yeah.

19:24.380 --> 19:27.427
I found a boot.
I need to see if it's a match.

19:31.257 --> 19:33.868
There might be another murder
in town.

19:33.911 --> 19:36.871
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

19:36.914 --> 19:38.220
<i>♪</i>

19:38.264 --> 19:39.656
- So you're telling me
eventually

19:39.700 --> 19:43.051
that thing
will look like that one?

19:43.094 --> 19:44.966
Where did you get the boot?

19:45.009 --> 19:48.274
- On the shore next to
Dr. Vanderspeigle's house.

19:48.317 --> 19:49.927
<i>♪</i>

19:49.971 --> 19:53.583
- So what happened to the real
Harry Vanderspeigle?

19:53.627 --> 19:54.932
<i>♪</i>

19:54.976 --> 19:56.717
- I don't know.

19:56.760 --> 19:58.371
<i>- I sort of broke
into Harry's house last night,</i>

19:58.414 --> 19:59.894
<i>and I saw a freezer
full of meat,</i>

19:59.937 --> 20:01.548
<i>and I thought
it was a dead body.</i>

20:01.591 --> 20:03.289
- Another murder is horrible,

20:03.332 --> 20:05.465
but we're gonna get
who did this.

20:05.508 --> 20:07.031
Promise.

20:07.075 --> 20:09.251
Okay?

20:09.295 --> 20:13.342
<i>♪</i>

20:13.386 --> 20:15.170
- [exhales sharply]

20:18.434 --> 20:21.350
<i>[upbeat music plays
through headset]</i>

20:21.394 --> 20:25.876
<i>♪</i>

20:25.920 --> 20:29.053
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

20:29.097 --> 20:33.884
<i>♪</i>

20:33.928 --> 20:35.408
- She has her earphones in.

20:35.451 --> 20:36.931
She can't hear anything.

20:36.974 --> 20:39.281
- I could scream louder
than her workout songs.

20:39.325 --> 20:41.240
I can get her down here
in two seconds!

20:41.283 --> 20:42.763
- Well, you're not gonna like
what happens to her

20:42.806 --> 20:44.068
when you do that.

20:44.112 --> 20:45.418
You need to tell us
where this alien is,

20:45.461 --> 20:48.595
you little shits.
- Why should we?

20:48.638 --> 20:51.424
- Because it's here
to kill us all.

20:51.467 --> 20:57.995
<i>♪</i>

20:58.039 --> 21:00.433
- If you think I am afraid
to kill everybody,

21:00.476 --> 21:02.739
you are dumb!

21:02.783 --> 21:06.003
I could press this button
at any time.

21:07.657 --> 21:08.919
If you agree with me

21:08.963 --> 21:10.965
and I am right
and you are wrong,

21:11.008 --> 21:15.578
then just sit there dead
and don't say anything.

21:15.622 --> 21:18.189
Okay, then.

21:18.233 --> 21:19.669
We agree.

21:19.713 --> 21:23.282
Goodbye, only human
in the room.

21:26.154 --> 21:28.809
[whirring]

21:28.852 --> 21:31.377
[loud buzz]

21:33.466 --> 21:35.598
[loud zap]

21:35.642 --> 21:37.948
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:37.992 --> 21:40.777
<i>That's impossible.</i>

21:40.821 --> 21:43.606
<i>The energy doesn't affect
my people.</i>

21:43.650 --> 21:44.912
<i>Was he right?</i>

21:44.955 --> 21:48.437
<i>Am I no longer my people?</i>

21:48.481 --> 21:51.658
<i>But that means
if I set off my device,</i>

21:51.701 --> 21:53.834
<i>it will kill me, too.</i>

21:53.877 --> 21:57.751
<i>♪</i>

21:57.794 --> 21:59.230
[vehicle door closes]

21:59.274 --> 22:01.363
- Hey.
[engine turning over]

22:01.407 --> 22:04.497
What are you doing out here?
[chuckles]

22:04.540 --> 22:05.976
- Nothing.

22:06.020 --> 22:08.805
Just making up nicknames
for everybody who walks by.

22:08.849 --> 22:12.331
Want to have a seat,
Mr. Short Pants?

22:12.374 --> 22:16.465
- Cool, guess I'll be throwing
these out when I get home.

22:16.509 --> 22:19.425
[sighs]

22:19.468 --> 22:20.687
[chuckles]

22:20.730 --> 22:23.211
This is the same bench
that we sat on

22:23.254 --> 22:26.823
that day we skipped
Mrs. Henderson's science class.

22:26.867 --> 22:29.652
- God, you're right.
[both chuckle]

22:29.696 --> 22:32.220
- That's a long time ago.

22:34.962 --> 22:36.790
- Are you okay?

22:36.833 --> 22:39.227
- I...

22:39.270 --> 22:42.491
remember being so happy
that day.

22:42.535 --> 22:45.842
That was right before
I left for Stratton.

22:45.886 --> 22:48.497
I remember feeling like...

22:48.541 --> 22:50.499
my life was just starting.

22:50.543 --> 22:54.547
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

22:54.590 --> 22:57.463
- Yeah, you've always
been happy like that.

22:57.506 --> 22:59.203
It's what I love about you.

22:59.247 --> 23:01.380
You know,
it's what everyone loves.

23:01.423 --> 23:03.251
<i>♪</i>

23:03.294 --> 23:04.861
- I'm not happy.

23:04.905 --> 23:06.210
<i>♪</i>

23:06.254 --> 23:09.213
- You're not?
- Are you?

23:09.257 --> 23:10.867
- Well, no.

23:10.911 --> 23:13.479
But I was never really happy
to begin with.

23:13.522 --> 23:15.437
- [chuckles]
- So...

23:15.481 --> 23:20.486
- Yeah, well, I had a chance
at being happy, but...

23:20.529 --> 23:22.879
it just went away, you know?

23:22.923 --> 23:26.361
I hurt my leg, and that was it.

23:26.405 --> 23:28.668
- Hey...
[scoffs]

23:28.711 --> 23:30.539
You can be happy.

23:30.583 --> 23:32.498
<i>♪</i>

23:32.541 --> 23:34.848
Look, I'm gonna play
the nickname game with you,

23:34.891 --> 23:38.895
and your nickname is Miss...

23:38.939 --> 23:40.767
You're Amazing.
[chuckles]

23:40.810 --> 23:42.246
- All right.

23:42.290 --> 23:44.727
Well, you're...
bad at that game.

23:44.771 --> 23:47.426
- [chuckles]
But it's true.

23:47.469 --> 23:50.907
I mean, you've accomplished
so much in your life.

23:50.951 --> 23:52.474
- Shut up.

23:52.518 --> 23:54.998
I-I'm not amazing.

23:55.042 --> 23:58.175
I-I feel like I've done
nothing with my life.

23:58.219 --> 23:59.742
I just...

23:59.786 --> 24:02.484
wanted to--

24:02.528 --> 24:04.181
I just wanted to matter...

24:04.225 --> 24:08.621
make a difference
to somebody, I--

24:08.664 --> 24:10.318
Maybe it's all just bullshit.

24:10.361 --> 24:12.451
- No, you matter.

24:12.494 --> 24:15.366
You're smart and funny.

24:17.456 --> 24:18.935
I-I wish I was like you.

24:18.979 --> 24:21.938
I'm terrified
of pretty much everything.

24:21.982 --> 24:25.768
But sometimes
I look at you, and...

24:25.812 --> 24:28.292
you're so fearless.

24:28.336 --> 24:32.514
It makes me feel,
I don't know, less scared.

24:32.558 --> 24:35.822
You know, you make me happy.

24:35.865 --> 24:38.041
Um...

24:38.085 --> 24:39.390
what are you doing?
- Sorry.

24:39.434 --> 24:40.957
- I'm married, D'arcy.
- Sorry about that.

24:41.001 --> 24:42.611
Yeah.
- Oh, my God.

24:42.655 --> 24:43.873
- I'm so sorry,

24:43.917 --> 24:45.396
I thought that--
- Uh, no, it's okay.

24:45.440 --> 24:47.790
I got to go.
- Right, right.

24:47.834 --> 24:49.879
Got to--got to go.

24:49.923 --> 24:51.446
Shit!

24:55.624 --> 24:56.886
Ahh.

24:56.930 --> 24:59.106
- Please, Max,
you have to trust me.

24:59.149 --> 25:01.630
He is going to kill everyone.

25:01.674 --> 25:02.805
Tell us who he is.

25:02.849 --> 25:04.720
- He's not going
to kill everyone.

25:04.764 --> 25:07.854
- His ship
is a Quimbaya amulet.

25:07.897 --> 25:09.899
- Max, he's going
to kill everyone.

25:09.943 --> 25:12.554
- He won't.
He'll listen to me!

25:12.598 --> 25:14.556
[footsteps approaching]

25:14.600 --> 25:17.167
- Why are you in my house?

25:17.211 --> 25:19.561
Sarah, what is going on?

25:21.171 --> 25:22.999
- "Hey, honey."

25:23.043 --> 25:25.088
"Good evening, sweetheart."

25:25.132 --> 25:27.047
"Oh, yeah, day was good.
What's for dinner?

25:27.090 --> 25:29.005
Divorce?
Great."

25:29.049 --> 25:34.750
<i>♪</i>

25:34.794 --> 25:37.057
Lock the door?
That's weird.

25:37.100 --> 25:38.537
<i>- Okay, take
whatever you want.</i>

25:38.580 --> 25:40.103
Please.
- Don't make me use this gun.

25:40.147 --> 25:41.670
- Oh, my God, oh, my God.
- Don't hurt the kids.

25:41.714 --> 25:43.150
<i>[line trilling]</i>

25:43.193 --> 25:45.500
- Mike, I need your help.
There's people in my house.

25:45.544 --> 25:47.371
My family is in there.
They have a gun.

25:47.415 --> 25:49.112
- What?
Okay, all right, look.

25:49.156 --> 25:50.461
Do not move.
Don't go inside.

25:50.505 --> 25:52.028
We'll be there in five minutes,
all right?

25:52.072 --> 25:53.464
- No, no, no, we don't have
five minutes.

25:53.508 --> 25:56.685
- Look, do not go inside!
We're on the way.

25:56.729 --> 25:57.991
Deputy!

25:58.034 --> 25:59.079
- Shit!

25:59.122 --> 26:00.689
- [shouting]

26:00.733 --> 26:02.430
- Shit!

26:02.473 --> 26:04.040
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

26:04.084 --> 26:05.172
[whispering]
Help.

26:05.215 --> 26:06.608
- Let me out of here!

26:06.652 --> 26:09.698
If you touch my kid,
I will kill you!

26:09.742 --> 26:11.874
- Max, who is that?

26:11.918 --> 26:14.877
Why is he wearing
a white coat, hmm?

26:14.921 --> 26:16.575
- Okay, I'll tell you.

26:16.618 --> 26:17.750
- I swear to God!

26:17.793 --> 26:20.056
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

26:20.100 --> 26:22.885
Get away from my kid!

26:22.929 --> 26:24.452
- Okay, he told us who it is.

26:24.495 --> 26:26.106
We got what we need.
Let's go.

26:26.149 --> 26:28.935
- Hold on, Max!
- Whoa, we're not doing that.

26:28.978 --> 26:30.632
- We're doing whatever
I say we're doing.

26:30.676 --> 26:32.634
[pounding on door]

26:32.678 --> 26:34.288
- [screams]

26:37.421 --> 26:38.597
- Get down.

26:43.558 --> 26:47.083
- [screaming]

26:47.127 --> 26:50.086
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

26:50.130 --> 26:52.262
<i>♪</i>

26:52.306 --> 26:55.135
<i>[Dr. Hook's
"Sharing the Night Together"]</i>

26:55.178 --> 26:58.617
<i>♪</i>

26:58.660 --> 27:01.750
<i>- ♪ Sharing the night
together ♪</i>

27:01.794 --> 27:04.927
<i>♪ Oh-oh, yeah</i>

27:04.971 --> 27:07.887
<i>♪ Sharing the night together</i>

27:07.930 --> 27:11.107
<i>♪ Oh-oh, yeah</i>

27:11.151 --> 27:14.067
<i>♪ Sharing the night together</i>

27:14.110 --> 27:17.374
<i>♪ Oh-oh, yeah</i>

27:17.418 --> 27:20.290
<i>♪ Sharing the night together</i>

27:20.334 --> 27:23.642
<i>♪ Oh-oh, yeah</i>

27:23.685 --> 27:26.296
<i>♪ Sharing the night together</i>

27:26.340 --> 27:28.821
<i>♪ Oh-oh, yeah</i>

27:28.864 --> 27:32.651
- You guys are like Daredevil
and the Black Widow.

27:32.694 --> 27:34.609
[both breathing heavily]

27:37.917 --> 27:39.962
- Thank you for saving my life.

27:40.006 --> 27:41.703
- Time to go.

27:41.747 --> 27:44.706
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

27:44.750 --> 27:47.709
<i>♪</i>

27:47.753 --> 27:49.842
- These things don't usually
have a happy ending.

27:49.885 --> 27:51.321
It could've been a lot worse.

27:51.365 --> 27:53.497
- Yeah, I don't recommend
citizens taking the law

27:53.541 --> 27:55.499
into their own hands,
but that was--

27:55.543 --> 27:58.633
that was some real hero shit
the two of you did in there.

27:58.677 --> 28:00.853
- Well, we're
a pretty good team.

28:00.896 --> 28:03.682
- Yes, we are.
- [chuckles]

28:03.725 --> 28:06.162
<i>♪</i>

28:06.206 --> 28:10.732
- You both have blood,
like, all over your shoes.

28:10.776 --> 28:13.300
- I'm never washing them.

28:13.343 --> 28:15.128
- Me neither.

28:15.171 --> 28:18.305
<i>[Dr. Hook's
"Sharing the Night Together"]</i>

28:18.348 --> 28:19.872
<i>♪</i>

28:19.915 --> 28:22.004
<i>- ♪ Sharing the night
together ♪</i>

28:22.048 --> 28:23.266
- Oh, no.

28:23.310 --> 28:25.878
<i>- ♪ Oh-oh, yeah</i>

28:25.921 --> 28:28.358
<i>♪ Sharing the night together</i>

28:28.402 --> 28:29.664
- That's a lot of tongue.

28:29.708 --> 28:31.535
- You trying to get
all the way in the back?

28:31.579 --> 28:32.667
Y'all nasty.
- Really?

28:32.711 --> 28:34.147
- Y'all got a room
right upstairs.

28:34.190 --> 28:36.627
- Oh, boy.

28:36.671 --> 28:39.587
<i>[slow music]</i>

28:39.630 --> 28:44.244
<i>♪</i>

28:44.287 --> 28:46.159
- How's that article coming?

28:46.202 --> 28:47.377
Need another quote?

28:47.421 --> 28:49.423
<i>♪</i>

28:49.466 --> 28:51.077
- Asta's my mother.

28:51.120 --> 28:53.340
- Yeah.
Sheriff Mike's my father.

28:53.383 --> 28:57.910
<i>♪</i>

28:57.953 --> 28:59.999
You--

29:00.042 --> 29:03.089
Holy shit.

29:03.132 --> 29:04.743
You're the baby.

29:06.222 --> 29:07.702
- I'm not surprised
she didn't tell you.

29:07.746 --> 29:10.357
She's been keeping it a secret.

29:10.400 --> 29:12.620
- Yeah.

29:12.663 --> 29:14.578
Yeah, she has.

29:14.622 --> 29:16.319
- I don't know what to do.

29:16.363 --> 29:17.799
She's my mother,

29:17.843 --> 29:19.888
and I don't even know
how to act in front of her.

29:19.932 --> 29:22.456
Not to mention my father.

29:22.499 --> 29:24.066
- Oh.

29:24.110 --> 29:25.328
Right.

29:25.372 --> 29:26.416
Jimmy.

29:26.460 --> 29:27.853
- It's so messed up.

29:27.896 --> 29:30.246
What am I supposed to say
to someone like that?

29:30.290 --> 29:32.292
I mean, I'm gonna see him.

29:32.335 --> 29:34.816
And I can't talk to Asta.
I can't talk to my parents.

29:34.860 --> 29:36.600
I probably shouldn't even be
talking to you right now,

29:36.644 --> 29:39.734
but I feel
like I am losing my mind

29:39.778 --> 29:41.823
and I need someone
in this town to talk to--

29:41.867 --> 29:44.478
- Hey, hey, hey.
Hey, hey, hey!

29:44.521 --> 29:46.523
You can totally talk to me.

29:46.567 --> 29:48.351
- I can't live here
like this, okay?

29:48.395 --> 29:50.614
I can't do--

29:50.658 --> 29:53.617
- You are not running away
from this.

29:53.661 --> 29:57.230
And you are not alone.

29:57.273 --> 29:58.797
I can help you.

29:58.840 --> 30:01.538
<i>♪</i>

30:01.582 --> 30:03.018
Hey.

30:04.541 --> 30:06.892
Can you get free onion rings?

30:06.935 --> 30:08.676
It's part of the plan.

30:08.719 --> 30:10.417
- [chuckles]

30:10.460 --> 30:14.160
<i>♪</i>

30:14.203 --> 30:15.683
Yeah, okay.

30:15.726 --> 30:19.600
<i>♪</i>

30:19.643 --> 30:20.949
[door slams]

30:20.993 --> 30:23.778
- You killed
Harry Vanderspeigle.

30:23.822 --> 30:25.867
- No, I didn't.

30:25.911 --> 30:28.827
- Do not lie to me.

30:28.870 --> 30:31.177
- Okay, I killed him,
but he started it.

30:31.220 --> 30:34.223
- Do you have any idea
what you did?

30:34.267 --> 30:36.922
You cannot just murder someone.
That is not how it works here.

30:36.965 --> 30:39.185
- Humans kill people
all the time.

30:39.228 --> 30:41.752
Someone killed
Sam Hodges, so...

30:41.796 --> 30:44.712
- Yeah, and you saw
what that did to me,

30:44.755 --> 30:47.758
to all of us,
and you did the same thing.

30:47.802 --> 30:48.890
[sighs]
No.

30:48.934 --> 30:50.805
Goodbye. This is done.

30:50.849 --> 30:53.416
We are done.
- No, don't say that.

30:53.460 --> 30:54.678
Wait, wait.
- What?

30:54.722 --> 30:56.550
What?

30:56.593 --> 30:59.988
- It'll be okay.
It's like the song.

31:00.032 --> 31:03.818
"Ooh, child, things are going
to get easier."

31:03.862 --> 31:05.951
"Ooh, child"--
Stop.

31:05.994 --> 31:07.953
- Don't touch me!
- I'm sorry.

31:07.996 --> 31:10.259
You just can't leave me.

31:10.303 --> 31:13.132
- Don't tell me
what I can and cannot do.

31:13.175 --> 31:14.655
Wow, you are really
getting a hang

31:14.698 --> 31:17.397
of this human-male bullshit.

31:17.440 --> 31:19.355
- Don't go.
It hurts!

31:19.399 --> 31:22.054
[cries]

31:22.097 --> 31:23.751
It's--

31:23.794 --> 31:26.754
it's you.

31:26.797 --> 31:28.103
You're the reason
that I feel it--

31:28.147 --> 31:30.845
the joy and the fury
all wrapped up.

31:30.889 --> 31:33.979
- You want fury?

31:34.022 --> 31:36.329
Go back to your planet, Harry.

31:36.372 --> 31:38.113
Whoever you are,

31:38.157 --> 31:40.724
whatever you are,
I never want to see you again.

31:40.768 --> 31:41.900
- But we are friends.

31:41.943 --> 31:44.424
- I am not friends
with people--

31:44.467 --> 31:46.078
I mean... not people.

31:46.121 --> 31:47.514
I don't know what you are.

31:47.557 --> 31:50.256
But I know what you're not.
You are not my friend.

31:50.299 --> 31:53.259
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

31:53.302 --> 31:55.174
<i>♪</i>

31:55.217 --> 31:56.523
[door slams]

31:56.566 --> 31:58.177
- I thought you were my friend.

31:58.220 --> 32:02.659
[crying]

32:02.703 --> 32:09.797
<i>♪</i>

32:14.193 --> 32:15.672
[cries]

32:15.716 --> 32:18.414
[sniffling]

32:18.458 --> 32:20.199
I do not like this.

32:20.242 --> 32:22.810
<i>♪</i>

32:22.853 --> 32:26.292
I don't like this place
anymore.

32:26.335 --> 32:29.251
[loud whirring]

32:32.907 --> 32:36.780
<i>- ♪ It's up in the morning,
it's on the downs ♪</i>

32:36.824 --> 32:40.784
<i>♪ And the little white clouds
like gambling lambs ♪</i>

32:40.828 --> 32:42.351
<i>♪ And I am a breathless</i>

32:42.395 --> 32:44.745
- Hey. <i>
- ♪ Over you</i>

32:44.788 --> 32:48.792
<i>♪ And the red-breasted robin
beats his wings ♪</i>

32:48.836 --> 32:53.058
<i>♪ His throat,
it trembles when he sings ♪</i>

32:53.101 --> 32:54.537
<i>♪ For he is helpless</i>

32:54.581 --> 32:57.366
- Hi. <i>
- ♪ Before you</i>

32:57.410 --> 32:59.194
- So, I, uh...

32:59.238 --> 33:01.370
I guess you're my father.

33:01.414 --> 33:04.634
- [chuckles]
Yeah.

33:04.678 --> 33:08.290
- If you ever touch Asta again,
I'll ------- kill you.

33:08.334 --> 33:10.292
<i>♪</i>

33:10.336 --> 33:12.425
- Feel better?

33:12.468 --> 33:14.079
- Oh, D'arcy,
what are you--

33:14.122 --> 33:16.298
D'arcy, don't!
Ugh!

33:16.342 --> 33:18.909
Son of a bi--

33:18.953 --> 33:20.172
D'arcy!

33:20.215 --> 33:23.305
Oh!
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

33:23.349 --> 33:25.046
<i>- ♪ And still your heart</i>

33:25.090 --> 33:27.048
- Oh, no! <i>
- ♪ And still your face</i>

33:27.092 --> 33:29.355
<i>♪ Comes shining through
- Look out!</i>

33:29.398 --> 33:32.140
Look out!
Out of the way!

33:32.184 --> 33:34.273
[loud crash]

33:34.316 --> 33:35.578
- Oh.

33:35.622 --> 33:37.189
<i>- ♪ And still your soul</i>

33:37.232 --> 33:40.105
- Yeah.
Yeah, I feel better.

33:40.148 --> 33:42.629
- Yeah, me too.
[chuckles]

33:42.672 --> 33:44.805
We--we should go now.

33:44.848 --> 33:46.807
<i>♪</i>

33:46.850 --> 33:48.461
[both giggle]

33:50.593 --> 33:53.770
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

33:53.814 --> 33:56.599
<i>♪</i>

33:56.643 --> 33:59.080
[phone buttons beeping]

33:59.124 --> 34:00.429
- [sighs]

34:00.473 --> 34:02.475
<i>[line trilling]</i>

34:02.518 --> 34:03.998
Miss Twelvetrees?

34:04.042 --> 34:06.087
Hey, it's Max Hawthorne.

34:06.131 --> 34:07.349
<i>I need your help.</i>

34:07.393 --> 34:08.916
<i>Harry's here to kill everyone,</i>

34:08.959 --> 34:11.223
<i>and I think I know
where he's going.</i>

34:11.266 --> 34:16.576
<i>♪</i>

34:19.187 --> 34:21.363
[soft whirring]

34:21.407 --> 34:22.843
[door closes]

34:25.150 --> 34:26.629
- Excuse me.

34:26.673 --> 34:28.805
Are you the town doctor?

34:28.849 --> 34:30.198
- Yes, I am.

34:30.242 --> 34:31.982
Oh, that is a nasty cut--

34:32.026 --> 34:33.419
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

34:33.462 --> 34:36.422
[straining]

34:36.465 --> 34:39.468
<i>♪</i>

34:39.512 --> 34:42.471
- [grunts]

34:42.515 --> 34:44.517
Town doctor.

34:44.560 --> 34:45.822
That kid was right.

34:45.866 --> 34:47.563
He is the prettiest alien
I've ever seen.

34:47.607 --> 34:48.738
- [chuckles nervously]

34:48.782 --> 34:50.088
Yeah.
Just be careful, all right?

34:50.131 --> 34:51.263
We don't know what this
monster's capable of.

34:51.306 --> 34:52.525
- Yeah.

34:52.568 --> 34:55.528
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

34:55.571 --> 34:59.140
<i>♪</i>

34:59.184 --> 35:03.144
- [grunting]

35:03.188 --> 35:05.407
[tires squealing]

35:05.451 --> 35:08.106
[engines roaring]

35:08.149 --> 35:10.499
[tires screeching]

35:10.543 --> 35:13.285
- Move, move. Let's go.
- Whoa.

35:13.328 --> 35:15.461
<i>♪</i>

35:15.504 --> 35:17.419
What--what the hell is this?

35:17.463 --> 35:19.421
<i>♪</i>

35:19.465 --> 35:21.380
- Come on.

35:21.423 --> 35:23.599
- I knew you were real.
- Okay.

35:23.643 --> 35:25.645
I-I got you your alien.

35:25.688 --> 35:28.778
So now I'm officially done
with her.

35:28.822 --> 35:31.172
- Aw.
- I'm sorry.

35:31.216 --> 35:33.000
This woman is...

35:33.043 --> 35:34.784
an unhinged psychotic.

35:34.828 --> 35:37.091
- [chuckles]
- I agree completely.

35:37.135 --> 35:38.527
- Close it up!

35:38.571 --> 35:40.486
<i>♪</i>

35:40.529 --> 35:42.052
- Wait, are you--are you guys
men in black?

35:42.096 --> 35:43.837
- Oh, would you stop it.
They're not called that.

35:43.880 --> 35:45.360
You've watched too many movies.

35:45.404 --> 35:47.145
And if I wanted them involved,

35:47.188 --> 35:50.191
I would've told my superiors.

35:50.235 --> 35:53.368
And then we wouldn't have
an alien, would we?

35:53.412 --> 35:54.804
- Who's we?

35:54.848 --> 35:57.720
- This is bigger than anything
you could imagine.

35:57.764 --> 36:01.376
Too bad you won't be here
to see how it all plays out.

36:01.420 --> 36:03.639
Get rid of him.

36:03.683 --> 36:05.859
- I told you.

36:05.902 --> 36:08.688
I have different orders.
- Okay, um...

36:08.731 --> 36:12.082
[laughter, indistinct chatter]

36:12.126 --> 36:14.650
<i>♪</i>

36:14.694 --> 36:16.391
- [scoffs]
Kill ya later.

36:16.435 --> 36:18.393
[engine turning over]

36:18.437 --> 36:21.309
<i>♪</i>

36:21.353 --> 36:24.269
- [breathing heavily]

36:24.312 --> 36:27.097
<i>♪</i>

36:27.141 --> 36:30.100
[tires squealing]

36:30.144 --> 36:32.581
- See, I don't get it.

36:32.625 --> 36:34.453
I mean, first Sam,
then this roving couple

36:34.496 --> 36:36.933
going around terrorizing
people.

36:36.977 --> 36:39.240
Don't get me wrong,
I like the mayhem.

36:39.284 --> 36:41.764
- Mm-hmm.
- I like it a lot.

36:41.808 --> 36:43.810
I might like it a little
too much, if that's possible.

36:43.853 --> 36:44.854
- It is.

36:44.898 --> 36:47.988
It's quite frightening,
actually.

36:48.031 --> 36:51.861
Don't forget the foot
with the matching boot.

36:51.905 --> 36:53.689
But...

36:53.733 --> 36:56.475
can it all really be
just a coincidence?

36:56.518 --> 36:57.693
- I don't believe
in coincidence.

36:57.737 --> 36:59.956
- Oh, me neither.

37:00.000 --> 37:02.611
- So both the boot
and the foot

37:02.655 --> 37:04.396
were found in the same area

37:04.439 --> 37:06.136
right by
Dr. Vanderspeigle's place.

37:06.180 --> 37:08.443
- Yeah, you mean the boot,
the foot, and the doorknob.

37:08.487 --> 37:11.185
That thing definitely didn't
come from no houseboat,

37:11.229 --> 37:12.839
that's for sure.

37:12.882 --> 37:15.407
Looks like we might have
a new prime suspect.

37:15.450 --> 37:16.886
Let's go visit
Dr. Vanderspeigle

37:16.930 --> 37:20.150
tomorrow morning, see
if he's got anything to add.

37:20.194 --> 37:22.283
<i>♪</i>

37:22.327 --> 37:24.285
- What is that?

37:24.329 --> 37:27.070
Oh!

37:27.114 --> 37:31.771
Oh...my ...d.

37:31.814 --> 37:33.468
Is this a Nespresso?

37:33.512 --> 37:34.687
- It's nothing, man.

37:34.730 --> 37:35.818
I just picked that up
for the office.

37:35.862 --> 37:37.385
It was on sale.
- Yes, yes!

37:37.429 --> 37:39.387
Oh, my God, oh, my God!

37:39.431 --> 37:40.823
You got me
a coffee pod machine!

37:40.867 --> 37:41.911
- Oh, what are you doing?

37:41.955 --> 37:42.999
I got that
for the whole office.

37:43.043 --> 37:44.784
What are you doing?
- Nope.

37:44.827 --> 37:46.786
You got it for me,

37:46.829 --> 37:50.006
and you agree
with my doorknob instincts.

37:50.050 --> 37:52.008
- You got decent
doorknob instincts, all right?

37:52.052 --> 37:53.401
But this whole thing
is for everybody.

37:53.445 --> 37:54.533
It ain't just for you.
- Nope.

37:54.576 --> 37:55.490
- What are you doing?
- Nope.

37:55.534 --> 37:57.187
You got it for me.

37:57.231 --> 38:00.147
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

38:00.190 --> 38:06.153
<i>♪</i>

38:11.376 --> 38:13.378
[indistinct shouting]

38:13.421 --> 38:15.336
[tires screeching]

38:15.380 --> 38:17.860
[alarms blaring]

38:17.904 --> 38:19.862
- You in the vehicle!

38:19.906 --> 38:22.038
Let me see your hands!

38:25.390 --> 38:26.521
[blaring continues]

38:26.565 --> 38:28.088
[loud whoosh]

38:28.131 --> 38:30.743
[men grunting]

38:30.786 --> 38:36.923
<i>♪</i>

38:38.403 --> 38:40.230
<i>- I have no choice now,</i>

38:40.274 --> 38:43.190
<i>since my device
will destroy me.</i>

38:43.233 --> 38:45.540
<i>I will fly away from here
and drop the device</i>

38:45.584 --> 38:49.544
<i>onto this beautiful planet
to finish the job I started.</i>

38:49.588 --> 38:52.634
[helicopter blades
whirring outside]

38:59.293 --> 39:01.817
<i>♪</i>

39:01.861 --> 39:05.038
[loud buzzing]

39:10.304 --> 39:17.267
<i>♪</i>

39:19.618 --> 39:21.097
- Whoa.

39:21.141 --> 39:26.886
<i>♪</i>

39:26.929 --> 39:29.454
[vehicles approaching]

39:29.497 --> 39:32.761
[tires squealing]

39:32.805 --> 39:34.328
- Go, go, go!

39:34.372 --> 39:37.331
[men shouting]

39:40.813 --> 39:43.642
- Double up, double up!

39:43.685 --> 39:44.817
- Harry!

39:44.860 --> 39:47.167
[men shouting]

39:47.210 --> 39:49.735
[whirring]

39:49.778 --> 39:51.563
- There's more!

39:51.606 --> 39:53.391
- Freeze!

39:53.434 --> 39:54.870
Hold it right there.

39:54.914 --> 40:00.441
<i>♪</i>

40:00.485 --> 40:02.008
- Oh, no.

40:03.444 --> 40:05.272
I forgot the pizzas.

40:07.883 --> 40:10.364
[tires squealing]

40:10.408 --> 40:12.497
<i>Maybe I can go back
and get them.</i>

40:12.540 --> 40:13.846
<i>I could take the ship</i>

40:13.889 --> 40:17.763
<i>and pick them up
on my way to space.</i>

40:17.806 --> 40:21.070
<i>I can't because
of this stupid mission.</i>

40:23.551 --> 40:25.858
<i>I am so hungry.</i>

40:27.076 --> 40:29.601
They look like black ants.

40:29.644 --> 40:36.651
<i>♪</i>

40:36.695 --> 40:38.914
Where is your queen?

40:38.958 --> 40:45.747
<i>♪</i>

40:45.791 --> 40:47.227
- Come on.

40:47.270 --> 40:54.234
<i>♪</i>

40:55.583 --> 40:58.499
- [sighs]
- Get down.

40:58.543 --> 40:59.848
- Harry!

40:59.892 --> 41:01.894
- [groans]

41:01.937 --> 41:05.071
[ship whirring]

41:06.768 --> 41:09.641
<i>[Five Stairsteps'
"O-o-h Child"]</i>

41:09.684 --> 41:16.778
<i>♪</i>

41:19.781 --> 41:22.044
<i>- ♪ Ooh, child</i>

41:22.088 --> 41:25.439
<i>♪ Things are gonna
get easier ♪</i>

41:25.483 --> 41:28.660
<i>♪ Ooh, child,
things will get brighter ♪</i>

41:28.703 --> 41:30.836
<i>♪</i>

41:30.879 --> 41:33.621
<i>♪ Ooh, child...</i>

41:33.665 --> 41:36.058
- Run, Max!
Hide!

41:36.102 --> 41:40.280
<i>- ♪ Ooh, child,
things will get brighter ♪</i>

41:40.323 --> 41:43.849
<i>♪</i>

41:43.892 --> 41:45.851
- Harry...

41:45.894 --> 41:47.983
I know why you're here.

41:48.027 --> 41:49.811
Don't do it.
Please don't do it.

41:49.855 --> 41:51.117
- I must.

41:51.160 --> 41:54.512
It's why I came here.
- I don't care.

41:54.555 --> 41:56.165
You're not the same.

41:56.209 --> 41:58.733
You've changed
since you came here,

41:58.777 --> 42:00.256
since you killed that man.

42:00.300 --> 42:02.911
I've seen it.
I just saw it now.

42:02.955 --> 42:05.610
You could've left,
but you stayed to help us.

42:05.653 --> 42:08.047
You've changed.
- No.

42:08.090 --> 42:11.311
My mission is to kill everyone.

42:11.354 --> 42:13.182
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

42:13.226 --> 42:15.228
- If you kill everyone,

42:15.271 --> 42:16.751
you kill me.

42:16.795 --> 42:21.930
<i>♪</i>

42:21.974 --> 42:25.543
- You are right,
I have changed, but--

42:25.586 --> 42:27.762
- There's my friend.

42:27.806 --> 42:30.591
- We are friends?

42:30.635 --> 42:32.637
- Yes.

42:32.680 --> 42:35.030
We are friends.

42:35.074 --> 42:37.119
<i>♪</i>

42:37.163 --> 42:41.036
- So, that means you will come
with me to my planet

42:41.080 --> 42:44.649
and we will kill everyone
on Earth together?

42:44.692 --> 42:46.825
- What?
No.

42:46.868 --> 42:49.871
I-I'm--I'm staying here.

42:49.915 --> 42:54.789
<i>♪</i>

42:54.833 --> 42:58.358
- Then I won't kill everyone.

42:58.401 --> 42:59.925
- [sighs]

42:59.968 --> 43:01.753
Okay, good.

43:01.796 --> 43:04.233
<i>♪</i>

43:04.277 --> 43:07.323
- I will miss you, friend.

43:07.367 --> 43:08.890
- I'll miss you, too, friend.

43:08.934 --> 43:11.066
[device speaks alien language]

43:11.110 --> 43:13.242
- I should dispose
of my device.

43:13.286 --> 43:15.984
It will kill everyone on Earth

43:16.028 --> 43:19.379
when it detonates
in 80 seconds.

43:19.422 --> 43:20.467
- Oh, my God.

43:20.510 --> 43:22.643
Yes.
Go.

43:22.687 --> 43:24.297
Go!

43:25.690 --> 43:27.822
[sighs]

43:27.866 --> 43:30.477
- Real quick...

43:30.520 --> 43:32.784
I left some pizzas

43:32.827 --> 43:35.874
in my freezer.

43:35.917 --> 43:38.441
You can have them
if you want them.

43:38.485 --> 43:39.878
- Thank you.

43:39.921 --> 43:42.663
Go!

43:42.707 --> 43:44.622
[sighs]

43:46.406 --> 43:53.326
<i>♪</i>

44:00.594 --> 44:03.553
[ship whirring]

44:03.597 --> 44:10.473
<i>♪</i>

44:13.607 --> 44:16.741
<i>- Everyone has to die
eventually.</i>

44:16.784 --> 44:21.397
<i>What matters are the choices
you make while you're alive.</i>

44:21.441 --> 44:24.400
<i>Killing may make humans
feel strong in the moment,</i>

44:24.444 --> 44:26.664
<i>but what I've begun
to realize is,</i>

44:26.707 --> 44:30.145
<i>true strength comes
from choosing not to kill.</i>

44:30.189 --> 44:31.973
<i>Maybe being truly human</i>

44:32.017 --> 44:34.759
<i>is about choosing to love
instead.</i>

44:34.802 --> 44:38.284
<i>[bright music]</i>

44:38.327 --> 44:40.199
<i>But with that love
comes the pain</i>

44:40.242 --> 44:42.070
<i>that I feel inside me.</i>

44:42.114 --> 44:44.203
<i>I need to go home.</i>

44:44.246 --> 44:46.074
<i>Hopefully the further
I get from them,</i>

44:46.118 --> 44:48.424
<i>the less I will care.</i>

44:48.468 --> 44:50.992
<i>Finally, I will be
at peace again.</i>

44:51.036 --> 44:53.778
[metal clanks]

44:53.821 --> 44:55.910
- [nervously]
Hi.

44:55.954 --> 44:58.913
You're taking me home, right?

44:58.957 --> 45:01.742
- This is some bullshit!

45:01.786 --> 45:02.961
Ugh.
